Dia. 03 Uncommon Maek
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Black 1 is an \cf1\b uncommon maek\cf0\b0 .
\par After White 2, Black takes with 3 and it becomes pae.
\par
\par Even if White takes at A, Black plays at B and it is pae again.
\par
\par Therefore White can't win the capturing race with 1 in the previous diagram.
\par
\par }
